Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.88,0:00:57.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,不喜歡坐飛機  是嗎?\N{\rENG}You don't like flying, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.25,0:01:01.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,不太喜歡\N{\rENG}What gives you that idea?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.42,0:01:08.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,想知道長途飛行的健身之道嗎?\N{\rENG}You wanna know the secret to surviving air travel?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.22,0:01:11.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,在到達目的地之後  把鞋和襪子脫掉\N{\rENG}After you get where you're going, take off your shoes and socks.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.26,0:01:15.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,然後光著腳在地毯上走走  把腳趾蜷起來\N{\rENG}Then you walk around on the rug barefoot and make fists with your toes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.80,0:01:18.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,把腳趾蜷起來?\N{\rENG}Fists with your toes?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.77,0:01:21.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的  聽起來很怪\N{\rENG}I know. It sounds crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.68,0:01:23.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,相信我  我已經做了九年了\N{\rENG}Trust me. I've been doing it for nine years.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.01,0:01:27.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的  先生  比洗澡和喝咖啡更有效\N{\rENG}Yes, sir! Better than a shower and a hot cup of coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.39,0:01:41.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,別害怕  我是員警\N{\rENG}It's OK. I'm a cop.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.29,0:01:47.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,相信我  我已經做了十一年了\N{\rENG}Trust me. I've been doing this for 11 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.40,0:01:52.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,我代表機長和工作人員歡迎  你們來洛杉磯\N{\rENG}The captain and the crew would like to welcome you to Los Angeles.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.40,0:01:55.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,祝大家聖誕快樂\N{\rENG}Have a very merry Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.40,0:02:02.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,虎膽龍威
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.68,0:02:07.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,搭乘247號航班飛往圖森的乘客  請在14號登機口登機\N{\rENG}Flight 247 to Tucson now boarding at gate 14.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.52,0:02:14.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,搭乘247號航班飛往圖森的乘客  請在14號登機口登機\N{\rENG}Flight 247 to Tucson now boarding at gate 14.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.02,0:02:44.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,女士先生們\N{\rENG}Ladies and gentlemen...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.82,0:02:46.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,女士先生們\N{\rENG}Ladies and gentlemen!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.22,0:02:51.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,我要祝賀你們大家  你們的努力\N{\rENG}I want to congratulate all of you for making this one of the greatest years...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.73,0:02:54.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,使今年成為  中富公司歷史上業績最好的一年\N{\rENG}in the history of the Nakatomi Corporation.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.00,0:03:03.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,我代表首席執行長和公司董事會\N{\rENG}On behalf of the Chief Executive Officer, Mr Ozu, and the Board of Directors,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.37,0:03:07.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,感謝大家  祝你們聖誕快樂  新年快樂\N{\rENG}we thank you all and wish you a merry Christmas and a happy New Year!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.64,0:03:09.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,聖誕快樂  新年快樂\N{\rENG}Merry Christmas! Happy New Year!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.81,0:03:14.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,荷莉  一起吃晚餐好嗎?\N{\rENG}Hey, Holly. What about dinner tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.42,0:03:17.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,哈裡  今天是聖誕夜\N{\rENG}Harry, it's Christmas Eve.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.05,0:03:19.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,家人  聖誕樹...\N{\rENG}Families, stockings...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.26,0:03:23.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,還有烤栗子?\N{\rENG}Chestnuts?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.49,0:03:28.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,馴鹿和雪人  你怎麼不想想這些?\N{\rENG}Rudolph and Frosty? Any of these things ring a bell?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.63,0:03:33.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,實際上  我想的是芬芳美酒  和美味乳酪\N{\rENG}Actually, I was thinking more of mulled wine, a nice, aged Brie
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.63,0:03:37.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,還有熊熊的爐火  你明白我的意思嗎?\N{\rENG}and a roaring fireplace. You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.07,0:03:43.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,吉妮  已經5點40了  去參加派對  喝點香檳吧\N{\rENG}Ginny, it's 5:40. Join the party. Have some champagne.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.51,0:03:46.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,別讓我覺得自己在壓榨屬下\N{\rENG}You're making me feel like Ebenezer Scrooge.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.25,0:03:49.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,非常感謝  你想胎兒會讓我喝兩杯吧?\N{\rENG}Thanks. Do you think the baby can handle a little sip?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.02,0:03:52.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,開酒館都沒問題\N{\rENG}That baby's ready to tend bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.69,0:03:54.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,最後的機會\N{\rENG}Last chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.66,0:03:55.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,再見\N{\rENG}Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.46,0:04:06.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,麥克萊恩家  我是露茜·麥克萊恩\N{\rENG}McClane residence. Lucy McClane speaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.02,0:04:09.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,你好  露茜·麥克萊恩  和你說話的是媽媽\N{\rENG}Hello, Lucy McClane. This is your mother speaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.07,0:04:13.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,媽咪!  你什麼時候回家?\N{\rENG}Mommy! When are you coming home?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.11,0:04:17.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,很快  不過到時候  你肯定已經睡了\N{\rENG}Pretty soon. You'll be in bed when I get there, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.15,0:04:19.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,讓鮑琳娜和我通話  好嗎?\N{\rENG}Let me talk to Paulina, OK, hon?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.75,0:04:24.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,不要在家裡轉來轉去找禮物哦\N{\rENG}And no snooping around the house looking for presents.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.22,0:04:26.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,爸爸和你一起回家嗎?\N{\rENG}Is Daddy coming home with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.82,0:04:30.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,我看還是...\N{\rENG}Well, we'll see what
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.76,0:04:33.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,讓聖誕老人和媽媽來決定吧\N{\rENG}Santa and Mommy can do, OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.36,0:04:35.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,叫鮑琳娜來  再見  寶貝\N{\rENG}Put Paulina on. Bye, honey.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.63,0:04:37.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,鮑琳娜\N{\rENG}Paulina!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.24,0:04:44.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,你好  荷莉太太\N{\rENG}Hola, Mrs Holly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.21,0:04:47.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,麥克萊恩先生來過電話嗎?\N{\rENG}Did Mr McClane call?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.18,0:04:49.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒有  荷莉太太  沒有電話\N{\rENG}No, Mrs Holly. No telefono.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.81,0:04:53.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,也許他上飛機前沒時間打\N{\rENG}He probably didn't have time before his flight.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.02,0:04:56.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,你最好還是把客房收拾好\N{\rENG}It might be a good idea to make up the spare bedroom
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.92,0:04:57.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,以防萬一\N{\rENG}just in case.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.02,0:05:00.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,是  荷莉太太  我已經收拾了\N{\rENG}Si, Mrs Holly. I do that already.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.06,0:05:04.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒有你我可怎麼辦  鮑琳娜?\N{\rENG}What would I do without you, Paulina?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.62,0:05:30.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,加州\N{\rENG}California!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.90,0:05:45.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是約翰·麥克萊恩\N{\rENG}Hey, I'm John McClane.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.07,0:05:48.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是阿蓋  你的包車司機\N{\rENG}Argyle. I'm your limo driver.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.87,0:05:53.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,漂亮的熊\N{\rENG}Nice bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.61,0:06:01.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,好吧  阿蓋  我們現在該幹什麼?\N{\rENG}OK... Argyle. What do we do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.65,0:06:06.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,我還以為你知道呢  我是第一次開這種車\N{\rENG}I was hoping you could tell me. It's my first time driving a limo.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.52,0:06:09.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒關係  這也是我第一次坐這種車\N{\rENG}That's OK. It's my first time riding in one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.82,0:06:12.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,放鬆  這裡要什麼有什麼\N{\rENG}Relax. We got everything in this mug.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.53,0:06:15.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,你看這兒...  CD  收音機  電視\N{\rENG}Look at this... CD, CB, TV,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.86,0:06:18.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,電話  小酒吧  錄影機\N{\rENG}telephone, full bar, VHS.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.10,0:06:25.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果你的朋友要發情  我還能幫他找頭母熊\N{\rENG}If your friend's hot to trot, I know a few mama bears we can hook up with.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.07,0:06:28.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,-或是說他結婚了?  -他結婚了\N{\rENG}- Or is he married? - He's married.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.48,0:06:35.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,真對不起  清潔工今天放假\N{\rENG}Sorry about that. It's the girl's day off.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.40,0:06:36.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒想到你會坐前排\N{\rENG}I didn't know you were gonna sit up front.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.65,0:06:39.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,你太太住在這兒?\N{\rENG}Your lady live out here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.55,0:06:41.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,差不多六個月了\N{\rENG}About the past six months.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.02,0:06:44.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,這麼說你還住在紐約\N{\rENG}Meaning you still live in New York?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.09,0:06:48.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,你總是有這麼多問題嗎  阿蓋?\N{\rENG}You always ask this many questions, Argyle?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.30,0:06:52.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,對不起  我以前開計程車  總喜歡和別人聊聊\N{\rENG}Sorry. I used to drive a cab and people would expect a little chitchat.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.03,0:06:54.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,你離婚了?\N{\rENG}- So, you divorced?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.78,0:06:56.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,開你的車吧  夥計\N{\rENG}- Just drive the car, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.40,0:07:00.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,說吧  你離婚了還是分居?  她打你嗎?\N{\rENG}Hey, come on. You divorced? You separated? She beat you up?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.14,0:07:07.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,她有份好工作  現在是事業有成\N{\rENG}She had a good job. It turned into a great career.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.32,0:07:09.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,所以她不得不搬到這兒\N{\rENG}That meant she had to move here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.28,0:07:14.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,-你腦子挺靈的  阿蓋  -那你幹嘛不到這來?\N{\rENG}- You're very fast, Argyle. - So, why didn't you come?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.69,0:07:20.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,你幹嘛不和她一起來  夥計怎麼了?\N{\rENG}Well? Why didn't you come with her? What's up?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.26,0:07:23.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,因為我是紐約員警\N{\rENG}Because I'm a New York cop.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.16,0:07:26.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,我還有一堆紐約人渣要抓\N{\rENG}I got a backlog of scumbags I'm still trying to put behind bars.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.97,0:07:28.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不能拍拍屁股就離開\N{\rENG}I can'tjust go that easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.07,0:07:31.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,換句話說  你覺得她在這兒不會成功\N{\rENG}You thought she wasn't gonna make it here
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.41,0:07:34.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,她會回去你身邊  那就不用收拾行李了  對吧?\N{\rENG}and she'd come crawling back to you so why bother to pack, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.08,0:07:39.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒錯  你的腦子確實很靈  阿蓋\N{\rENG}Like I said, you're very fast, Argyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.48,0:07:40.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,聽聽音樂可以嗎?\N{\rENG}Mind if we hear some tunes?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.39,0:07:46.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,真不錯\N{\rENG}Hey, that'll work.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.26,0:07:50.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,聽聽聖誕歌曲好嗎?\N{\rENG}Don't you got any Christmas music?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.93,0:07:53.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,這就是聖誕歌曲\N{\rENG}This is Christmas music.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.62,0:08:25.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,等一下你太太見到你  你們緊緊擁抱\N{\rENG}So your lady sees you, you run into her arms,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.33,0:08:28.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,接著音樂響起  從此就幸福生活  是嗎?\N{\rENG}the music comes up and you live happily ever after, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.10,0:08:31.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,這個計畫不錯\N{\rENG}I can live with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.97,0:08:35.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果這招不管用  你要找個地方住嗎?\N{\rENG}So, if it doesn't work out, you got a place to stay?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.90,0:08:38.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,對  我要找個地方\N{\rENG}I'll find a place.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.61,0:08:41.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,那這樣吧  我把車開到車庫去等著\N{\rENG}I tell you what. I'll wait in the parking garage.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.85,0:08:44.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,要是成了  就打電話給我\N{\rENG}You score, give me a call on the car phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.11,0:08:48.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,我會把你的包放在前臺  要是沒成功  我就幫你找家旅館\N{\rENG}I'll take your bags to the desk. You strike out, I'll get you a hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.05,0:08:53.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,-你這人不錯  阿蓋  -給小費的時候別忘了就行\N{\rENG}- You're all right, Argyle. - Remember that when you sign for the tip.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.14,0:09:19.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,-嗨  -晚上好\N{\rENG}- Hi. - Good evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.48,0:09:21.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,我來找荷莉·麥克萊恩\N{\rENG}I'm here to see Holly McClane.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.55,0:09:23.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,打在那上面就行了\N{\rENG}Just type it in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.86,0:09:31.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,可愛的玩具\N{\rENG}Cute toy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.09,0:09:35.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,是啊  上廁所時  還能幫你拉拉鍊\N{\rENG}Yeah, if you have to take a leak, it'll even help you find your zipper.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.18,0:09:53.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,天啊\N{\rENG}Christ!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.25,0:10:00.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,-第三十層  -開派對那層\N{\rENG}- Thirtieth floor? - The party.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.81,0:10:02.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在這座樓裡就剩他們了\N{\rENG}They're the only ones left in the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.52,0:10:06.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,乘快速電梯  聽到嘈雜聲就到了\N{\rENG}Take the express elevator. Get off where you hear the noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.33,0:10:07.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝\N{\rENG}Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.09,0:11:08.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,-香檳?  先生  -謝謝\N{\rENG}- Champagne, sir? - Yeah, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.96,0:11:44.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,哦  對不起\N{\rENG}Oh, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.43,0:11:47.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,聖誕快樂!\N{\rENG}Hey! Merry Christmas!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.60,0:11:53.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,老天!\N{\rENG}Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.03,0:11:55.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,該死的加州人\N{\rENG}Fuckin' California!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.98,0:12:03.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,嗨  我正在找...\N{\rENG}Hi. I'm looking for...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.71,0:12:05.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,-荷莉·吉奈蘿?  -對\N{\rENG}- Holly Gennero. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.18,0:12:07.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,您肯定是約翰·麥克萊恩\N{\rENG}Then you must be John McClane.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.21,0:12:09.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是青木  那輛車還可以嗎?\N{\rENG}Joe Takagi. How was your ride in?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.65,0:12:12.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,很好  是您安排的嗎?\N{\rENG}Nice. I have you to thank for that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.25,0:12:14.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,那是最起碼我能做的\N{\rENG}Seemed the least we could do.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.39,0:12:15.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,-這地方真的不錯  -等完工後會更好的\N{\rENG}Quite a place you have.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.86,0:12:20.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,還有幾層沒有建好\N{\rENG}It will be if we get it finished. Still several floors under construction.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.39,0:12:24.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,荷莉到下面去傳真一些檔  她馬上就回來\N{\rENG}Holly went to fax some documents. She should be back any minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.27,0:12:26.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,這邊請  她的辦公室就在這兒\N{\rENG}In the meanwhile, her office is back here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.80,0:12:30.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,艾利斯?\N{\rENG}Ellis?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.31,0:12:35.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,我剛想打個電話  這兒的電話最近\N{\rENG}I was making a call. This was the nearest phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.84,0:12:38.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,這位是約翰·麥克萊恩\N{\rENG}I want you to meet John McClane,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.55,0:12:40.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,荷莉的丈夫\N{\rENG}Holly's husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.65,0:12:42.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,一位警官\N{\rENG}Holly's policeman.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.62,0:12:44.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,艾利斯負責國際發展部\N{\rENG}Ellis is in charge of international development.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.99,0:12:47.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,久仰您的大名\N{\rENG}Heard a lot about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.35,0:12:49.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒擦乾淨\N{\rENG}You missed some.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.69,0:12:52.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,您想吃點什麼嗎?\N{\rENG}Can I get you anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.49,0:12:55.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,食物  糕點  摻水的香檳?\N{\rENG}Food? Cake? Some watered-down champagne?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.63,0:12:57.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,不用  謝謝  我不餓\N{\rENG}No, thank you. I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.20,0:13:00.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,真是盛大的聚會\N{\rENG}You throw quite a party.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.40,0:13:05.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒想到日本人也過耶誕節\N{\rENG}I didn't realize they celebrated Christmas in Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.37,0:13:09.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們善於變通  珍珠港沒有成功  我們就傾銷電器\N{\rENG}We're flexible. Pearl Harbor didn't work out, so we got you with tape decks.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.28,0:13:14.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,實際上  今天是雙喜臨門\N{\rENG}It's sort of a double celebration.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.34,0:13:16.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們今天做成了一筆大買賣\N{\rENG}We closed a pretty big deal today
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.25,0:13:17.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,荷莉是主要的功臣  我正想...\N{\rENG}and a lot of it was due to Holly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.82,0:13:21.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,我可要失陪了\N{\rENG}I'll be out in a couple of minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.59,0:13:26.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,約翰...\N{\rENG}John.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.07,0:13:33.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,和大家見過面了?\N{\rENG}Have you met everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.07,0:13:35.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒有  我們正在監視他\N{\rENG}We've been sticking him with spears.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.10,0:13:37.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,開個玩笑\N{\rENG}Of course he has.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.81,0:13:40.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,她是一名商業天才  非常強硬\N{\rENG}She was made for the business. Tough as nails.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.04,0:13:43.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,我正希望你有趕上那班飛機\N{\rENG}I was hoping you made that flight.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.84,0:13:46.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,給他看看那個表\N{\rENG}Show him the watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.55,0:13:48.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,等會兒\N{\rENG}Later.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.12,0:13:52.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,給他看看  你不好意思嗎?  這是對她...\N{\rENG}Show him. Are you embarrassed? It's a small token of appreciation
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.09,0:13:55.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,努力工作的一點獎賞  是勞力士手錶\N{\rENG}for all her hard work. It's a Rolex.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.62,0:13:58.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,我想以後會見到的\N{\rENG}I'm sure I'll see it later.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.16,0:14:01.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,這兒有能梳洗的地方嗎?\N{\rENG}Is there a place where I could wash up?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.33,0:14:02.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,當然\N{\rENG}Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.35,0:14:22.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,你得原諒艾利斯  他每年這個時候都很沮喪\N{\rENG}You have to forgive Ellis. He gets very depressed this time of year.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.78,0:14:26.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,他總是認為自己的天賦最高  明白嗎?\N{\rENG}He thought he was God's greatest gift, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.12,0:14:28.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,我知道這種人\N{\rENG}I know the type.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.52,0:14:31.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,我想他看上你了\N{\rENG}I think he's got his eye on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.59,0:14:35.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒什麼  我看上了他的私人浴室\N{\rENG}That's OK. I have my eye on his private bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.56,0:14:38.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,你要住在哪兒?  事發突然...\N{\rENG}Where are you staying? Things happened so fast
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.73,0:14:41.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,我還來不及打電話問你\N{\rENG}I didn't get a chance to ask you on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.57,0:14:44.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,凱皮·羅伯茨退休到了這兒\N{\rENG}Cappy Roberts retired out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.77,0:14:49.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,-他說我可以去他那兒住  -凱皮退休了  他住在哪兒?\N{\rENG}- He said I could bunk with him. - Cappy retired, huh? Where's he live?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.51,0:14:51.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,拉摩納\N{\rENG}Romona.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.95,0:14:52.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,是帕摩納\N{\rENG}Pomona.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.21,0:14:55.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,帕摩納\N{\rENG}Pomona.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.48,0:14:57.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,-帕摩納  -對\N{\rENG}- Pomona. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.22,0:15:00.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,天哪  那樣時間都花在車上了\N{\rENG}You'll be in the car half the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.02,0:15:05.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們還是簡單一點吧  我有一個空房間\N{\rENG}Why don't we make it easy? I have a spare bedroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.63,0:15:08.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,雖然它不算大\N{\rENG}It's not huge or anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.50,0:15:11.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,可是孩子們願意和你在一起\N{\rENG}but the kids would love to have you at the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.03,0:15:14.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們願意嗎?\N{\rENG}They would, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.91,0:15:19.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,我也願意\N{\rENG}I would, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.41,0:15:24.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,對不起\N{\rENG}Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.79,0:15:34.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,我想你\N{\rENG}I missed you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.76,0:15:43.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,但是不包括我的姓氏在內  是不?\N{\rENG}Didn't miss my name, though, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.73,0:15:46.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,也許在簽支票的時候能想起來\N{\rENG}Except maybe when you're signing checks?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.20,0:15:49.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,你什麼時候開始姓吉奈蘿了?\N{\rENG}Since when did you start using Ms Gennero?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.44,0:15:55.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是一家日本公司  他們認為  已婚女人不可靠...\N{\rENG}This is a Japanese company. They figure a married woman's...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.04,0:15:58.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,你是結過婚的  荷莉  你嫁給我了\N{\rENG}You are a married woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.21,0:16:02.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,-你怎麼又說起這個了?  -我們還沒有談完\N{\rENG}- This conversation again? - We never finished this conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.05,0:16:08.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,-我有了一次機會  必須把握它  -對  不管是什麼結果\N{\rENG}- I had an opportunity. I had to take it. - No matter what it did to our marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.39,0:16:10.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,也許它改變了你對婚姻的理解\N{\rENG}It changed your idea of our marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.54,0:16:12.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,你根本對我的理解不瞭解...\N{\rENG}You have no clue what my idea...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.63,0:16:16.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,我完全清楚你對婚姻的理解\N{\rENG}I know exactly what your idea of our marriage should be.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.26,0:16:18.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,吉奈蘿小姐  我...\N{\rENG}Ms Gennero, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.80,0:16:21.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,對不起\N{\rENG}Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.04,0:16:23.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,嗨\N{\rENG}Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.67,0:16:29.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,青木先生正在找你  他想讓你給大家說幾句\N{\rENG}Mr Takagi is looking for you. He wants you to say something to the troops.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.44,0:16:30.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝\N{\rENG}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.88,0:16:36.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,我要走了\N{\rENG}Speech time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.85,0:16:39.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,我一會兒就回來\N{\rENG}Be back in a few minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.53,0:16:52.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,真是好樣的  約翰\N{\rENG}That was great, John.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.23,0:16:55.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,幹的好  真成熟\N{\rENG}Good job. Very mature.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.95,0:17:50.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,賈霸奪下籃板  傳給沃斯  接著是格林  再傳詹森\N{\rENG}So Kareem rebounds. Feeds Worthy on the break, over to AC, to Magic,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.12,0:17:51.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,又傳給沃斯\N{\rENG}then back to Worthy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.25,0:17:54.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,砰!  兩分\N{\rENG}Boom! Two points.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.37,0:18:00.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,行了\N{\rENG}We're in.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.10,0:19:13.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,自底層至29層關閉
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.00,0:20:51.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,太平洋電話公司雇員專用
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.19,0:21:08.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,真傻\N{\rENG}Son of a bitch.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.96,0:21:14.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,把腳趾頭蜷起來\N{\rENG}Fists with your toes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.43,0:21:46.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,阿蓋?\N{\rENG}Yeah, Argyle?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.03,0:21:48.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,你的事怎麼樣了?\N{\rENG}How's it going?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.63,0:21:49.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,很好  你在哪兒?\N{\rENG}All right. Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.96,0:21:52.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,我在車庫享受呢  你和太太說了些什麼?\N{\rENG}Down at the garage. What's with you and your lady?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.90,0:21:55.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,還沒定下來呐\N{\rENG}The vote's not in yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.20,0:22:28.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,阿蓋\N{\rENG}Argyle?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.84,0:22:30.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,麥克  怎麼了?  喂!\N{\rENG}Mac, you there? Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.55,0:22:41.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,你知道號碼  我等著\N{\rENG}You know the number. Use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.77,0:24:16.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,保持鎮靜  沒事的\N{\rENG}Stay calm. Everything's going to be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.74,0:24:18.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒事的\N{\rENG}Everything's going to be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.00,0:24:39.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,媽的\N{\rENG}Shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.74,0:24:43.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,冷靜\N{\rENG}Think.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.37,0:24:45.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,冷靜\N{\rENG}Think.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.76,0:25:04.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,女士先生們\N{\rENG}Ladies and gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.83,0:25:07.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,女士先生們\N{\rENG}Ladies and gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.80,0:25:19.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,由於中富公司在全球的  長期貪婪掠奪\N{\rENG}Due to the Nakatomi Corporation's legacy of greed around the globe
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.17,0:25:23.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們將遭到強大力量的懲罰\N{\rENG}they're about to be taught a lesson in the real use of power.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.48,0:25:26.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,你們將做為見證人\N{\rENG}You will be witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.88,0:25:29.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在...\N{\rENG}Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.98,0:25:32.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,請問哪位是青木先生?\N{\rENG}where is Mr Takagi?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.49,0:25:38.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,約瑟夫·高木\N{\rENG}Joseph Yashinobo Takagi,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.36,0:25:42.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,1937年生於京都\N{\rENG}born Kyoto, 1937.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.40,0:25:44.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,別動\N{\rENG}Don't move.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.76,0:25:48.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,全家於1939年  移民至加州的聖佩德羅\N{\rENG}Family emigrated to San Pedro, California, 1939,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.90,0:25:54.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,1942年至1943年在拘留營度過\N{\rENG}interned at Manzanar, 1942 to '43,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.78,0:26:01.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,1955年獲得加州大學的獎學金\N{\rENG}scholarship student, University of California, 1955.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.00,0:26:10.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,1962年獲史丹福大學法學學位\N{\rENG}Law degree, Stanford, 1962.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.80,0:26:14.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,1970年哈佛工商管理碩士學位\N{\rENG}MBA, Harvard, 1970.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.50,0:26:17.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,中富貿易公司總裁\N{\rENG}President, Nakatomi Trading.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.80,0:26:21.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,中富投資集團副主席\N{\rENG}Vice Chairman, Nakatomi Investment Group...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.20,0:26:22.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,夠了\N{\rENG}Enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.40,0:26:24.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,為人之父\N{\rENG}And father
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.61,0:26:26.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,有五個孩子\N{\rENG}of five.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.21,0:26:28.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,我就是青木\N{\rENG}I am Takagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.24,0:26:31.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,你好\N{\rENG}How do you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.85,0:26:34.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,很高興認識您\N{\rENG}It's a pleasure to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.56,0:26:50.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,32樓還沒完工  33樓是電腦室\N{\rENG}32... construction, 33... computers.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.51,0:27:05.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,漂亮的西裝\N{\rENG}Nice suit.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.85,0:27:07.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,約翰·飛利浦  倫敦\N{\rENG}John Phillips, London.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.32,0:27:12.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,我也有兩套\N{\rENG}I have two myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.05,0:27:15.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,據說阿拉法特也在那兒買衣服\N{\rENG}Rumor has it Arafat buys his there.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.89,0:27:23.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,-這邊嗎?  -向左轉\N{\rENG}- This way? - On the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.72,0:27:49.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,"當亞歷山大見到他遼闊的帝國時\N{\rENG}"And when Alexander saw the breadth of his domain...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.52,0:27:53.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,他哭了  因為他已經無可征服"\N{\rENG}he wept, for there were no more worlds to conquer."
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.93,0:28:00.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,這就是古典教育的好處\N{\rENG}The benefits of a classical education.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.84,0:28:04.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,真是太美了\N{\rENG}That's beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.61,0:28:09.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,我小的時候也喜歡做模型\N{\rENG}I always enjoyed to make models when I was a boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.38,0:28:14.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,精確無誤  不能放過任何細節\N{\rENG}The exactness, the attention to every conceivable detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.98,0:28:16.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,太美了\N{\rENG}It's beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.62,0:28:21.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,這就是你來的目的?  我們在印尼的計畫?\N{\rENG}Is this what this is all about? Our project in Indonesia?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.19,0:28:24.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,你和同夥們都想錯了\N{\rENG}Contrary to what you people may think,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.16,0:28:27.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們想發展那個地區  而不是剝削\N{\rENG}we're going to develop that region, not exploit it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.36,0:28:31.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,我完全相信  我讀過《福布斯》雜誌的報導\N{\rENG}I believe you. I read the article in Forbes.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.00,0:28:35.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,青木先生\N{\rENG}Mr Takagi...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.07,0:28:40.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,我可以談上一整天  工業化和男性時裝\N{\rENG}I could talk about industrialization and men's fashions all day...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.94,0:28:42.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,但是我想工作更重要\N{\rENG}but I'm afraid work must intrude...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.04,0:28:46.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,我的同事西奧有些問題要問你\N{\rENG}and my associate here has some questions for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.98,0:28:49.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,實際上是要你做幾道填空題\N{\rENG}Sort of fill-in-the-blanks questions, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.39,0:29:01.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,我沒有這密碼!\N{\rENG}I don't have that code.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.23,0:29:05.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,你們闖進來就是為了電腦?\N{\rENG}You broke in here to access our computer?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.97,0:29:09.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,你們得到的任何資訊  明天早上都會被東京方面更改\N{\rENG}Any information you get, when they wake up in Tokyo, they'll change it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.27,0:29:12.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,你根本無法勒索我方高層  威脅或者敲詐...\N{\rENG}You won't be able to blackmail our executives...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.27,0:29:14.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,坐下!\N{\rENG}Sit... down!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.22,0:29:28.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,青木先生  我對你的電腦不感興趣\N{\rENG}Mr Takagi, I'm really not interested in your computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.09,0:29:35.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,但是我需要密碼\N{\rENG}But I need the code key
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.70,0:29:40.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,我感興趣的是你鎖在金庫裡\N{\rENG}because I am interested in the $640 million...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.20,0:29:44.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,價值6.4億美元的可轉讓債券\N{\rENG}in negotiable bearer bonds that you have locked in your vault...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.67,0:29:48.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,而金庫受電腦控制\N{\rENG}and the computer controls the vault.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.51,0:29:51.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,你們只要錢\N{\rENG}You want money?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.95,0:29:54.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,你們算什麼恐怖分子\N{\rENG}What kind of terrorists are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.62,0:30:00.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,誰說我們是恐怖分子\N{\rENG}Who said we were terrorists?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.57,0:30:22.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,這筆債券最多也只有\N{\rENG}The bonds represent, at most,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.44,0:30:26.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,您們財團十天的運作資金\N{\rENG}10 days' operating capital for your parent organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.31,0:30:29.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,小菜一盤\N{\rENG}It's really no more than a temporary inconvenience.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.72,0:30:30.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在...\N{\rENG}Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.15,0:30:36.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,請說出密碼\N{\rENG}The code, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.26,0:30:41.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,你有密碼也沒用  金庫共有七道安全設施\N{\rENG}It's useless to you. There are seven safeguards on our vault.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.56,0:30:44.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,密碼只是其中一道  你永遠也打不開\N{\rENG}The code key's only one of them. You won't get it open.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.33,0:30:47.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,那您就更沒有理由  不告訴我們了\N{\rENG}Then there's no reason not to tell it to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.73,0:30:51.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,-不出所料  -還沒完呢\N{\rENG}- I told you. - It's not over yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.28,0:30:59.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,您的西裝很漂亮  青木先生\N{\rENG}It's a very nice suit, Mr Takagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.68,0:31:03.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,弄髒了會很可惜\N{\rENG}It would be a shame to ruin it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.12,0:31:08.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,我會從一數到三\N{\rENG}I'm going to count to three.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.52,0:31:12.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,絕不會有四\N{\rENG}There will not be a four.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.99,0:31:15.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,說出密碼\N{\rENG}Give me the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.30,0:31:17.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,一\N{\rENG}One,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.53,0:31:21.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,二\N{\rENG}two,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.80,0:31:25.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,-三  -我說過了  我不知道\N{\rENG}- three... - I don't know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.61,0:31:28.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,坐飛機到東京去問社長吧\N{\rENG}Get on ajet to Tokyo and ask the chairman.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.94,0:31:30.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,聽我說  你只能殺了我\N{\rENG}You'll just have to kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.18,0:31:31.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rENG}OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.95,0:31:37.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,看來只好費些力氣了\N{\rENG}We do it the hard way.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.45,0:31:39.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,托尼  你來打掃這裡\N{\rENG}Tony, dispose of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.55,0:31:42.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,卡爾  你最好到設備層去  檢查一下亨利的進展\N{\rENG}Karl, check on Heinrich up on the machine floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.28,0:32:09.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒人\N{\rENG}Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.15,0:32:11.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,去找亨利\N{\rENG}See to Heinrich.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.39,0:32:14.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在...\N{\rENG}Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.25,0:32:17.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,你能破解密碼嗎?\N{\rENG}you can break the code?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.39,0:32:22.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,你帶我來只是因為我的  相貌英俊嗎?\N{\rENG}You didn't bring me along for my charming personality.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.03,0:32:32.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,阿蓋  希望你聽到槍聲  正在報警\N{\rENG}Argyle, tell me you heard the shots. You're calling the police right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.61,0:32:36.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,我當然會去找你\N{\rENG}Of course I'm still coming by later.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.31,0:32:39.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,寶貝  我以前騙過你嗎?\N{\rENG}Sweetheart, have I ever lied to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.25,0:32:41.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,我的老闆?  他還以為我去了賭城呢\N{\rENG}My boss thinks I'm on my way to Vegas.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.05,0:32:45.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,尤裡  爬到管道上面去\N{\rENG}Uli, get up on the pipes.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.29,0:32:48.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,馬可  你到對面去\N{\rENG}Marco, you go through here.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.26,0:32:51.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,我把導線扔給你\N{\rENG}I'll throw you the cord.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.03,0:32:57.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,漢斯  我們在樓頂\N{\rENG}Hans, we're on the roof.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.04,0:33:12.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,接著\N{\rENG}Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.85,0:33:17.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,抓到了  尤裡\N{\rENG}Uli.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.46,0:33:25.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,破解密碼需要三十分鐘\N{\rENG}30 minutes to break the code,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.93,0:33:31.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,五道機械鎖則需要  至少兩到兩個半小時\N{\rENG}two hours, two and a half hours for the five mechanicals, at the minimum.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.36,0:33:34.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,但是第七道鎖  我也無法對付\N{\rENG}The 7th lock, however, is out of my hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.19,0:33:58.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,你說什麼?\N{\rENG}I'm sorry?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.69,0:34:02.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,第七道鎖  是電磁密封裝置\N{\rENG}The 7th lock... the electromagnetic seal.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.20,0:34:04.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,在這裡面無法切斷電路\N{\rENG}The circuits cannot be cut locally.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.40,0:34:07.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,相信我\N{\rENG}Trust me.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.47,0:34:12.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,你他媽的為什麼不阻止他們  約翰\N{\rENG}Why the fuck didn't you stop him, John?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.61,0:34:16.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,因為這樣你也死定了  是嗎?\N{\rENG}'Cause then you'd be dead, too, asshole.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.54,0:34:18.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,冷靜  混蛋  冷靜!\N{\rENG}Think, goddamn it! Think!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.92,0:34:32.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,樓內有火警警報\N{\rENG}We've got a fire alarm.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.23,0:34:34.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,打911\N{\rENG}Call 911.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.99,0:34:39.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,告訴他們警衛的名字  和消防密碼  取消警報\N{\rENG}Give them the guard's name and cancel the alarm.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.35,0:34:41.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,然後毀掉火警系統\N{\rENG}Then disable the sys...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.80,0:34:46.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,艾迪  警報是哪一層發出的?\N{\rENG}Eddie, on what floor did the alarm go off?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.24,0:34:50.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們能走了嗎?\N{\rENG}Shall we go?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.96,0:35:04.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,行\N{\rENG}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.39,0:35:07.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,過來  寶貝  到爸爸這來\N{\rENG}Hello, baby. Come to Papa. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.06,0:35:12.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,寶貝  過來\N{\rENG}Come on, baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.00,0:35:14.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,寶貝  寶貝  過來  寶貝!\N{\rENG}Come on, baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.23,0:35:18.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,到爸爸這來  讓我親親你他媽的小狗\N{\rENG}Come on, baby. Come to Papa. I'll kiss your fuckin' Dalmatian.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.94,0:35:23.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,你們這些蠢貨\N{\rENG}You stupid motherfuckers! No! No!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.81,0:35:25.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,不!  把車頭掉過來\N{\rENG}Turn the fuckin' truck around!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.21,0:36:02.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,火警已經解除了  朋友\N{\rENG}The fire has been called off, my friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.89,0:36:09.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒人會來幫你的\N{\rENG}No one is coming to help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.29,0:36:16.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,你應該出來和大家在一起\N{\rENG}You might as well come out and join the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.20,0:36:21.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,我保證絕不傷害你\N{\rENG}I promise I won't hurt you.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.83,0:36:53.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,放下槍  白癡  我是員警\N{\rENG}Drop it, dickhead. It's the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.07,0:36:55.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,你不會傷害我\N{\rENG}You won't hurt me.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.90,0:36:57.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,是嗎?  為什麼?\N{\rENG}Yeah? Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.77,0:36:59.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,因為你是員警\N{\rENG}Because you're a policeman.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.74,0:37:02.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,員警要遵守規定\N{\rENG}There are rules for policemen.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.24,0:37:05.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,對  我的上司也這麼說\N{\rENG}Yeah, that's what my captain keeps telling me.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.43,0:38:10.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,密碼有效  一號鎖解除
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.12,0:38:12.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,繼續操作嗎?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.41,0:38:14.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,大傻瓜  當然繼續\N{\rENG}Bet your ass I wish to proceed.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.89,0:38:56.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,全世界有900萬恐怖分子\N{\rENG}Nine million terrorists in the world...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.96,0:39:00.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,我卻殺了一個  腳比我妹妹還小的傢伙\N{\rENG}and I gotta kill one with feet smaller than my sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.48,0:39:54.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,我希望這是一次  職業的  有效的  合作性的接觸\N{\rENG}I wanted this to be professional, efficient, adult, cooperative.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.21,0:39:56.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,不要問的太多\N{\rENG}Not a lot to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.12,0:39:58.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,可惜  你們的青木先生不這樣看\N{\rENG}Mr Takagi did not see it that way...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.42,0:40:02.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,所以他的餘生無法和大家在一起了\N{\rENG}so he won't be joining us for the rest of his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.22,0:40:06.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,事態的發展是由你們決定的\N{\rENG}We can go any way you want it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.33,0:40:10.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,你們可以走出去  也可以被抬出去\N{\rENG}You can walk out of here or be carried out...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.30,0:40:14.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,請不要心存幻想  我們是主宰者\N{\rENG}but have no illusions... we are in charge.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.83,0:40:19.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在大家來決定吧\N{\rENG}So... decide now, each of you...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.91,0:40:21.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,請記住...\N{\rENG}and please remember...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.31,0:40:25.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,任何可能的情況我們都考慮到了\N{\rENG}we have left nothing to chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.79,0:40:35.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,拿回來!\N{\rENG}Get them back!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.96,0:40:47.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,"現在我有一支機關槍"\N{\rENG}"Now I have a machine gun."
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.31,0:40:57.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,是漏網的警衛?\N{\rENG}A security guard we missed?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.38,0:41:02.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,警衛都是吃養老金的胖老頭  不  肯定另有他人\N{\rENG}They're usually tired, old policemen. No, this is something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.16,0:41:14.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們必須採取措施  漢斯\N{\rENG}We have to do something, Hans.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.36,0:41:15.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的  是的\N{\rENG}Yes, we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.69,0:41:20.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,告訴卡爾  他弟弟死了  叫他下來\N{\rENG}Tell Karl his brother is dead. Tell him to come down.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.17,0:41:27.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,法蘭柯  你和佛裡把屍體抬到樓上\N{\rENG}Franco, Fritz, take the body upstairs and out of sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.94,0:41:31.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不要讓人質亂想\N{\rENG}I don't want the hostages to think too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.04,0:42:36.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,我要報仇!\N{\rENG}I want blood!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.88,0:42:39.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,會有機會的!  不過先讓亨利裝好炸藥\N{\rENG}You'll have it, but let Heinrich plant the detonators...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.05,0:42:42.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,弄開金庫  我們報警後\N{\rENG}and Theo prepare the vault. After we call the police,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.72,0:42:45.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,到時你要把大樓拆了都行\N{\rENG}you can tear the building apart looking for this man...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.02,0:42:48.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,在那之前  我們不能改變計畫!\N{\rENG}but, until then, do not alter the plan!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.29,0:42:51.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果他改變我們的計畫呢?\N{\rENG}And if he alters it?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.33,0:42:58.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,你認為是怎麼回事?\N{\rENG}What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.20,0:43:02.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,有些不對頭\N{\rENG}Something's wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.40,0:43:03.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,也許\N{\rENG}Cops?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.64,0:43:08.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,-是約翰  -約翰?\N{\rENG}- John. - John?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.44,0:43:11.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,他會把一切都搞糟的!  他以為自己在幹什麼?\N{\rENG}He can fuck this up. What does he think he's doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.01,0:43:13.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,在工作\N{\rENG}His job.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.35,0:43:17.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,胡鬧!  他的工作在三千英里之外\N{\rENG}Bullshit. His job's 3,000 miles away.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.08,0:43:21.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒有他  我們還有機會離開這個地方\N{\rENG}Without him, we still have a chance to get out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.45,0:43:23.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,去跟青木說吧\N{\rENG}Tell that to Takagi.
