Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.44,1:19:08.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,你一定要堅持住  聽到了嗎\N{\rENG}So hang in there, man, you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:08.11,1:19:10.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,你要堅持住\N{\rENG}You hang in there.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.61,1:19:14.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,明白  謝謝  夥計\N{\rENG}Yeah, thanks, partner.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.02,1:19:21.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,你在幹什麼?\N{\rENG}What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.45,1:19:25.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不想坐在這兒  看誰先把我們殺死\N{\rENG}I'm tired of sitting here waiting to see who gets us killed first,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.33,1:19:26.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們還是你丈夫\N{\rENG}them or your husband.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.93,1:19:28.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,你到底想幹什麼?\N{\rENG}What are you going to do?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:28.60,1:19:31.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,我一頓飯就能談下百萬美元\N{\rENG}I negotiate million-dollar deals for breakfast.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.42,1:19:34.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,難道連這些人渣都對付不了?\N{\rENG}I think I can handle this Eurotrash.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:34.10,1:19:37.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,談談怎麼樣\N{\rENG}Hey, sprechen sie talk, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:37.07,1:19:39.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,要是聽我的  他早就被困住了\N{\rENG}If you'd listened to me, he would be neutralized already.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:40.04,1:19:42.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不想困住他  我要他死\N{\rENG}I don't want neutral. I want dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:43.14,1:19:45.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,我沒有打攪你們吧\N{\rENG}Hope I'm not interrupting.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.14,1:19:46.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,他想要什麼\N{\rENG}What does he want?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.28,1:19:49.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,不是我想要什麼  而是我能給你們什麼\N{\rENG}It's not what I want. It's what I can give you.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.36,1:19:59.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,聽著  我還是直說了吧\N{\rENG}Look, let's be straight, OK?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:00.96,1:20:04.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,很明顯  你們到這來不只是  為了偷幾個小錢  對嗎?\N{\rENG}It's obvious you're not some dumb schmuck up here to snatch a few purses.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:04.50,1:20:06.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,你很會觀察\N{\rENG}You're very perceptive.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.23,1:20:07.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,我有在看"六十分鐘"\N{\rENG}I watch 60 Minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:07.97,1:20:10.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,我對自己說: "這些人都是行家\N{\rENG}I say to myself, these guys are professional,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:10.74,1:20:13.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們有動機  他們有計劃"\N{\rENG}they're motivated, they're happening,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.27,1:20:14.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們想要什麼東西\N{\rENG}they want something.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.94,1:20:17.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,我個人並不關心你們的政治信仰\N{\rENG}I couldn't care less about your politics.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.84,1:20:20.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,也許你們對阿拉伯人不滿\N{\rENG}Maybe you're pissed off at the camel jockeys.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:20.15,1:20:23.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,也許是以色列或是北愛  這不關我的事\N{\rENG}Maybe it's Northern Ireland. It's none of my business.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:23.15,1:20:26.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,你們是來談判的  沒錯吧\N{\rENG}I figure you're here to negotiate, am I right?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:26.06,1:20:27.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,令人驚訝\N{\rENG}You're amazing.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.13,1:20:29.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,全部是你自己想出來的?\N{\rENG}You figured this all out already?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:29.19,1:20:31.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,生意就是生意\N{\rENG}Hey, business is business.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:31.39,1:20:34.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,你們用槍  我用筆  有什麼區別?\N{\rENG}You use a gun, I use a fountain pen. What's the difference?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:34.73,1:20:37.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,我這樣說吧  你們的目的是錢\N{\rENG}In my terms, you're here on a hostile takeover.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.40,1:20:42.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,你計畫好一切  但沒想到有一顆老鼠屎壞事\N{\rENG}You grab us for some greenmail but didn't expect a poison pill to be running around.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:42.44,1:20:43.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,對嗎?\N{\rENG}Am I right?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.95,1:20:45.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,漢斯\N{\rENG}Hans,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.37,1:20:46.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,老弟\N{\rENG}bubbee,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.94,1:20:48.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,我就是你的白騎士\N{\rENG}I'm your white knight.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:50.60,1:20:52.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,我沒看過"六十分鐘"\N{\rENG}I must have missed "60 Minutes".
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.58,1:20:53.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,你是什麼意思?\N{\rENG}What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.02,1:20:59.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,樓上那傢伙壞了你們的事  嗯?\N{\rENG}The guy upstairs who's fucking things up, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:03.62,1:21:05.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,我可以把他交給你\N{\rENG}I can give him to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.43,1:21:14.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,羅伊  你還好嗎\N{\rENG}Roy? Roy, you all right?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.24,1:21:19.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,這些餅乾比我還老\N{\rENG}Just trying to fire down a 1,000-year-old Twinkie.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.50,1:21:22.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,裡面都放的什麼東西?\N{\rENG}What do they put in them?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.24,1:21:27.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,高糖麵粉  氫化植物油...\N{\rENG}Sugar-enriched flour, partially hydrogenated vegetable oil,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.25,1:21:28.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,聚山梨醇酯60\N{\rENG}polysorbate 60,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:28.78,1:21:30.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,五號黃色色素\N{\rENG}and yellow dye number five.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.80,1:21:33.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,孩子發育需要的一切營養\N{\rENG}Just everything a growing boy needs.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:34.33,1:21:36.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,你有多少個孩子  艾爾?\N{\rENG}How many kids you got, Al?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.27,1:21:40.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,事實上  我的妻子正懷第一個\N{\rENG}As a matter of fact, my wife is working on our first.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.40,1:21:42.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,你呢  牛仔?\N{\rENG}How about you, cowboy?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.14,1:21:44.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,你的農場裡有孩子嗎?\N{\rENG}You got any kids back on your ranch?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.84,1:21:47.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,有\N{\rENG}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.65,1:21:48.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,兩個\N{\rENG}Two.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:49.15,1:21:53.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,希望他們以後  能和你兒子一起蕩秋千\N{\rENG}Sure hope I can see them swinging on ajungle gym with Al Jnr someday.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:55.75,1:21:57.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,那就說定了\N{\rENG}Well, now, that's a date...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:57.59,1:21:59.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,不過你可要帶霜淇淋來\N{\rENG}but you bring the ice cream.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.19,1:22:02.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,感人  牛仔  非常感人\N{\rENG}Touching, cowboy. Touching.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.36,1:22:04.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,也許我該叫你\N{\rENG}Or should I call you...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.76,1:22:06.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,麥克萊恩先生?\N{\rENG}Mr McClane?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.20,1:22:10.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,紐約警察局的\N{\rENG}Mr Officer John McClane
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.97,1:22:13.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,約翰·麥克萊恩警官\N{\rENG}of the New York Police Department?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.21,1:22:17.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,給紐約的哈裡打電話\N{\rENG}Get on the phone to Harry in New York.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.54,1:22:19.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,你讓指揮中心的人查一查\N{\rENG}You better get hold of somebody at Dispatch.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:20.01,1:22:24.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,德蕾莎修女在三年級時  叫我麥克萊恩先生\N{\rENG}Sister Theresa called me Mr McClane in the third grade.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.52,1:22:28.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,我的朋友們叫我約翰  你誰也不是  人渣\N{\rENG}My friends call me John... and you're neither, shithead.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.89,1:22:35.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,這有個人想和你談談  一位特殊的朋友\N{\rENG}I have someone who wants to talk to you. A very special friend...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.56,1:22:38.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,晚會上和你在一起的\N{\rENG}who was with you at the party tonight.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:44.14,1:22:46.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,嘿  約翰兄\N{\rENG}Hey, John boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:47.54,1:22:49.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,艾利斯?\N{\rENG}Ellis?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:49.27,1:22:50.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,對\N{\rENG}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.68,1:22:54.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在聽著  約翰  他們給我幾分鐘讓我跟你說話\N{\rENG}Listen, John, they're giving me a few minutes to talk sense into you.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:54.71,1:22:57.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,我知道你認為自己在盡職\N{\rENG}I know you think you're doing yourjob...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:57.88,1:23:02.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,我表示感謝  但你讓情況變得複雜\N{\rENG}but you're just dragging this out. No one gets out of here until these guys
Dialogue: 0,1:23:02.75,1:23:04.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,讓這些人和洛杉磯員警談判\N{\rENG}can talk to the LA police.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.56,1:23:07.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,你必須停止搗亂  否則誰也甭想出去  明白嗎?\N{\rENG}That won't happen until you stop messing up the works.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:13.50,1:23:15.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,艾利斯  你對他們說過什麼?\N{\rENG}Ellis, what have you told them?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.70,1:23:18.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,我說我們是老朋友\N{\rENG}I told them we were old friends and...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.28,1:23:20.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,而今天晚上你是我的客人\N{\rENG}you were my guest at the party.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.60,1:23:23.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,艾利斯  你不該這麼做\N{\rENG}Ellis, you shouldn't be doin' this.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.08,1:23:25.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,這個不用你說?\N{\rENG}Tell me about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.95,1:23:33.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,好了  約翰  聽著\N{\rENG}All right, John, listen.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.50,1:23:36.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們想讓你說出雷管的下落\N{\rENG}Tell them where the detonators are.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.02,1:23:39.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們知道有人在聽\N{\rENG}They know people are listening.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:39.36,1:23:43.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們需要雷管  否則他們會殺了我\N{\rENG}They want the detonators, or they're gonna kill me.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:46.60,1:23:48.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,約翰  你聽見了嗎?\N{\rENG}John, didn't you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.74,1:23:52.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,對  我聽見了\N{\rENG}Yeah, I hear you.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:52.70,1:23:54.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,約翰  我想你還是別管閒事了\N{\rENG}John, I think you could get out the program a little.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.76,1:23:56.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,員警已經到了  這是他們的事\N{\rENG}The police are here now. It's their problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.99,1:23:59.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,告訴他們雷管在哪兒  就沒有人會受傷!\N{\rENG}Tell them where the detonators are!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:59.98,1:24:02.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,知道嗎  我是在為你賭命  老兄\N{\rENG}I'm putting my life on the line for you, pal!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.11,1:24:04.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,艾利斯  你仔細地聽我說\N{\rENG}Ellis, listen to me carefully.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:05.05,1:24:05.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,約翰...\N{\rENG}John...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:05.78,1:24:07.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,閉嘴  艾利斯!  馬上給我閉嘴!\N{\rENG}Shut up, Ellis! Just shut your mouth!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.55,1:24:09.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,把對講機交給漢斯\N{\rENG}Put Hans back on.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.05,1:24:14.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,漢斯  這個蠢貨不瞭解情況  但我知道  聽著\N{\rENG}Hans, this shithead does not know what kind of man you are but I do.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.73,1:24:18.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,很好  那就交出雷管  拯救你朋友的生命\N{\rENG}Then you'll give us what we want and save your friend's life.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:18.26,1:24:20.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,這件事與你毫無關係\N{\rENG}You're not part of this equation.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:20.56,1:24:22.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,那我呢?\N{\rENG}Hey, what am I, a method actor?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.97,1:24:26.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,老兄  把槍拿開  這是對講機  不是電視\N{\rENG}Babe, put away the gun. This is radio, not television.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:26.37,1:24:30.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,漢斯  這個混蛋不是我朋友!  我們剛碰面  我根本不認識他\N{\rENG}Hans, this asshole is not my friend! I don't know him!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.07,1:24:35.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,艾利斯  這些人會殺了你!  告訴他們你不認識我!\N{\rENG}Jesus Christ, Ellis! These people will kill you! Tell them you don't know me!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:35.21,1:24:37.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,這麼多年的交情  怎麼能這麼說?\N{\rENG}How can you say that after all these years?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.68,1:24:41.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,約翰  約翰?\N{\rENG}John? John?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.68,1:25:05.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,你聽見啦?\N{\rENG}Do you hear that?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:06.61,1:25:09.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,告訴我  我的雷管在哪兒?\N{\rENG}Talk to me! Where are my detonators?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.48,1:25:12.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,說出來  否則我就再殺一個\N{\rENG}Where are they, or shall I shoot another one?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.18,1:25:16.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,遲早會輪到你真正關心的人\N{\rENG}Sooner or later, I might get to someone you do care about.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.65,1:25:18.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,去你媽的  漢斯\N{\rENG}Go fuck yourself, Hans.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.46,1:25:22.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,聽到嗎  是他害死了那個人\N{\rENG}He just let the guy die.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.63,1:25:24.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,他不管他的死活  把對講機給我\N{\rENG}He gave him up. Give me that headset.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.73,1:25:26.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,這和親手扣扳機沒什麼兩樣\N{\rENG}That's like pulling the trigger yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.93,1:25:30.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,難道你不知道是怎麼回事嗎?  難道你看不出來嗎?\N{\rENG}Can't you see what's happening? Can't you read between the lines?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.67,1:25:33.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,他盡了一切努力去救他!\N{\rENG}He did everything he could to save him.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.07,1:25:36.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果他投降  那麼他倆都已經死了!\N{\rENG}If he gave himself up, they'd both be dead right now!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:36.27,1:25:38.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,不行  不行  他們要和我們談判\N{\rENG}No way, man. They'd be talking to us.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.04,1:25:42.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,聽著  告訴你那位夥伴  從現在開始別再插手  你聽見了嗎?\N{\rENG}You tell this partner of yours to stay out of this from now on.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:42.61,1:25:46.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,要是他不聽  我就要他好看  聽著  我會給他好看的\N{\rENG}Because if he doesn't, I'm really going to nail his ass.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:46.25,1:25:49.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,他已經受傷  孤單又疲憊\N{\rENG}The man is hurting. He is alone, tired,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:49.49,1:25:53.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,下面的這些人卻無所事事\N{\rENG}and he hasn't seen diddly-squat from anybody here!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.26,1:25:55.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在你卻站在這兒告訴我\N{\rENG}You're gonna tell me he'll give a damn...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:55.83,1:25:59.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,就算他能活著出來  你也要給他好看?\N{\rENG}about what you do to him if he makes it out of there alive?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:59.10,1:26:02.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,好好想想自己說的這些屁話\N{\rENG}Why don't you wake up and smell what you shovelin'?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.10,1:26:03.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,你給我聽著  警官\N{\rENG}You listen to me, sergeant.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.73,1:26:07.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,你要是想回家  隨時可以辭職\N{\rENG}Any time you want to go home, you consider yourself dismissed.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.51,1:26:10.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,不  長官  你甭想趕我走!\N{\rENG}No, sir. You couldn't drag me away.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:10.74,1:26:12.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,警方注意\N{\rENG}Attention, police.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.78,1:26:15.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,警方注意\N{\rENG}Attention, police.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.98,1:26:19.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,-我是艾爾·鮑爾警官  -把它給我\N{\rENG}- This is Sergeant Al Powell... - Give me that.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:19.18,1:26:21.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是  這是副局長  杜恩·羅賓森\N{\rENG}This is Deputy Chief Dwayne Robinson.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.75,1:26:22.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,你是誰?\N{\rENG}Who is this?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.75,1:26:24.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是漢斯·格魯伯\N{\rENG}This is Hans Gruber.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.56,1:26:29.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,我想你們  已經知道進攻我們的直接後果\N{\rENG}I assume you realize the futility of direct action against me.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.16,1:26:31.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們不想再有人喪命\N{\rENG}We have no wish for further loss of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.16,1:26:34.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,你到底想要什麼  格魯伯先生?\N{\rENG}What is it you do wish for?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.30,1:26:38.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,我的同志  正在世界各地受牢獄之苦\N{\rENG}I have comrades in arms around the world languishing in prison.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.60,1:26:42.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,美國政府不是  喜歡到處炫耀武力嗎?\N{\rENG}The American State Department enjoys rattling its saber for its own ends.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.41,1:26:44.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在為我炫耀一回吧\N{\rENG}Now it can rattle it for me.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.88,1:26:50.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,以下這些人必須被立即釋放\N{\rENG}The following people are to be released from their captors.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.15,1:26:53.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,北愛爾蘭扣押的  七名愛爾蘭共和軍成員\N{\rENG}In Northern Ireland the seven members of the New Provo Front.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.95,1:26:57.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,加拿大扣押的五名  魁北克解放運動領導人\N{\rENG}In Canada, the five imprisoned leaders of Liberte de Quebec.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.30,1:27:02.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,斯里蘭卡扣押的  九名亞洲曙光運動組織成員\N{\rENG}In Sri Lanka, the nine members of the Asian Dawn.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.13,1:27:03.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,搞什麼鬼?\N{\rENG}What the fuck?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.69,1:27:05.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,亞洲曙光運動?\N{\rENG}Asian Dawn?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.60,1:27:08.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,我在《時代》雜誌上看到的\N{\rENG}I read about them in Time magazine.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.60,1:27:12.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,這些革命的兄弟姐妹  重獲自由以後\N{\rENG}When these revolutionary brothers and sisters are free,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.20,1:27:15.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,這裡的人質將被押到大廈樓頂\N{\rENG}the hostages in this building will be taken to the roof...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.51,1:27:20.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們將和我們一起乘直升機  到達洛杉磯國際機場\N{\rENG}and they will accompany us in helicopters to the Los Angeles International Airport
Dialogue: 0,1:27:20.24,1:27:22.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,到那裡後  我再告訴你下一步該怎麼做\N{\rENG}where they will be given further instructions.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.95,1:27:24.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,你們有兩個小時的時間\N{\rENG}You have two hours to comply.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.92,1:27:28.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,等等  稍等一下  格魯伯先生\N{\rENG}Wait a minute. Mr. Gruber. This is crazy.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.45,1:27:32.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,我  我  我沒有這個權力  兩個小時根本不夠\N{\rENG}I don't have the authority. Two hours is not enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.32,1:27:34.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,喂   喂?\N{\rENG}Hello? Hello!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:36.66,1:27:39.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,你都錄下來了嗎?  我們去打幾個電話\N{\rENG}Did you get all that? We got to make some calls.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:39.93,1:27:42.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,你以為他們會照辦嗎?\N{\rENG}Do you think they'll even try?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:42.17,1:27:43.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,管他呢?\N{\rENG}Who cares?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.57,1:27:48.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,西奧  進展如何?\N{\rENG}Theo, are we on schedule?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:48.81,1:27:50.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,還有一道鎖  然後就看你的了\N{\rENG}One more to go, then it's up to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:50.84,1:27:54.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,最好你是對的  要打開最後一道  只能靠奇跡了\N{\rENG}You better be right, because the last one will take a miracle.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:54.38,1:27:55.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,今天是耶誕節  西奧\N{\rENG}It's Christmas, Theo.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.98,1:27:58.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,是奇跡的節日  保持愉快的心情\N{\rENG}It's the time of miracles, so be of good cheer
Dialogue: 0,1:27:58.62,1:28:01.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,解最後一道鎖的時候再告訴我\N{\rENG}and call me when you hit the last lock.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.15,1:28:03.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,卡爾\N{\rENG}Karl,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:03.25,1:28:06.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,幹掉那個小混蛋  把雷管奪回來\N{\rENG}hunt that little shit down and get those detonators.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.99,1:28:09.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,佛裡正在檢查炸藥\N{\rENG}Fritz is checking the explosives.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.23,1:28:11.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,我去檢查炸藥  你只管奪回雷管\N{\rENG}I'll check the explosives. You get the detonators.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.83,1:28:14.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,夥計  你還在嗎?\N{\rENG}Hey, Powell, you out there?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.70,1:28:17.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,我在這兒  約翰  我在這兒\N{\rENG}I'm here, John. I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:17.90,1:28:20.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,你必須相信我  我已經無能為力了\N{\rENG}You gotta believe me. There was nothing I could do.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:22.44,1:28:25.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,要是你錯了  我們倆都得倒楣\N{\rENG}Well, it's gonna be both our asses if you're wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:25.28,1:28:26.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,我明白\N{\rENG}I hear you.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:32.72,1:28:35.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,你聽見漢斯的那套鬼話了嗎?\N{\rENG}Did you catch that bullshit Hans was running?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:36.21,1:28:37.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,不太對頭  夥計\N{\rENG}It doesn't make sense, man.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:39.09,1:28:43.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,不要問我  我只是一個  在你求救時正想回家的員警\N{\rENG}Don't ask me. I'm just a deskjockey who was on my way home when you rang.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.23,1:28:46.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,看你開車的樣子  還以為你是個巡警\N{\rENG}The way you drove that car, I figured you for the street, Al.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:46.90,1:28:49.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,我年輕的時候曾經是\N{\rENG}In my youth. In my youth.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:50.33,1:28:54.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,《人質與恐怖分子雙向研究》\N{\rENG}author of "Hostage Terrorist, Terrorist Hostage:
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.20,1:28:55.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,的作者海瑟多夫博士\N{\rENG}A Study in Duality."
Dialogue: 0,1:28:55.47,1:28:59.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,海瑟多夫博士  你預期接下來的幾小時會怎麼樣?\N{\rENG}Dr Hasseldorf, what can we expect in the next few hours?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.27,1:28:59.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,蓋兒  在這個時候...\N{\rENG}Well, Gail,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.91,1:29:02.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,人質將經歷\N{\rENG}by this time, the hostages should be going through
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.61,1:29:04.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,赫爾辛基症候群的早期階段\N{\rENG}the early stages of the Helsinki Syndrome.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.94,1:29:06.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,就是瑞典的赫爾辛基\N{\rENG}As in Helsinki, Sweden.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.88,1:29:08.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,是芬蘭\N{\rENG}Finland.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:08.55,1:29:12.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,基本上  人質與恐怖分子\N{\rENG}Basically, it's when the hostages and the terrorists
Dialogue: 0,1:29:12.25,1:29:14.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,將經歷某種心理轉移\N{\rENG}go through a sort of psychological transference
Dialogue: 0,1:29:14.95,1:29:17.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,並產生彼此依賴的感覺\N{\rENG}and a projection of dependency.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.16,1:29:20.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,發展出某種奇怪的信任與友情\N{\rENG}A strange sort of trust and bond develops.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.09,1:29:22.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,在某些案例中  人質在獲釋後...\N{\rENG}We've had situations where the hostages
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.76,1:29:25.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,會擁抱綁架者\N{\rENG}have embraced their captors after release
Dialogue: 0,1:29:25.17,1:29:27.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,甚至和獄中的他們通信\N{\rENG}and even corresponded with them in prison.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:27.77,1:29:30.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,不  寶貝  是亞洲曙光\N{\rENG}No, no, darling. Asian Dawn. Dawn.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.64,1:29:33.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,曙光\N{\rENG}D-A-W-N.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:33.67,1:29:35.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,-長官?  -什麼?\N{\rENG}- Sir? - Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:35.18,1:29:36.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,聯邦調查局的人來了\N{\rENG}Sir, the FBI is here.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:37.00,1:29:39.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,-他們來了?  -對  長官  就在那邊\N{\rENG}- The FBI is here now? - Yes, sir. Right over there.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:41.08,1:29:42.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,拿著\N{\rENG}Hold this.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.52,1:29:44.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,不來點口香糖嗎?\N{\rENG}Want a breath mint?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:48.79,1:29:50.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,你還好嗎  夥計?\N{\rENG}Hey, how you doing, man?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.26,1:29:53.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是探員強森  這位是特別探員強森\N{\rENG}I'm Agent Johnson. This is Special Agent Johnson.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.96,1:29:57.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,-你們好嗎?  -不是親戚\N{\rENG}- Oh, how you doing? - No relation.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:00.13,1:30:03.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是杜恩·羅賓森  洛杉磯警察局的  負責這裡\N{\rENG}I'm Dwayne Robinson, LAPD. I'm in charge here.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:04.07,1:30:06.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,不再是了\N{\rENG}Not anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.83,1:31:04.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,夥計  你好\N{\rENG}Hi, there. How you doin'?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.34,1:31:13.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,天啊!  你是他們一夥的  對嗎?\N{\rENG}Please, God. No. You're one of them, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:13.57,1:31:15.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,你是他們一夥的\N{\rENG}You're one of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:15.21,1:31:18.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,別殺我  求求你!\N{\rENG}No! Don't kill me! Please!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:18.18,1:31:20.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,別殺我!  求求你!\N{\rENG}Don't kill me, please! Please, please, please.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:20.75,1:31:23.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,放鬆!  我不會傷害你\N{\rENG}Whoa. Relax. I'm not gonna hurt you.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:23.58,1:31:25.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不會傷害你!\N{\rENG}I'm not gonna hurt you!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:27.82,1:31:29.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,我的天\N{\rENG}Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.89,1:31:36.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,你在這上面幹什麼?  你在找什麼?\N{\rENG}What the fuck are you doin' up here? What were you lookin' for?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.20,1:31:38.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,我設法逃了出來  我...\N{\rENG}I managed to get out of there and
Dialogue: 0,1:31:38.70,1:31:41.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,我想逃到樓頂\N{\rENG}I was just trying to get up on the roof
Dialogue: 0,1:31:41.90,1:31:44.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,看看能否發出求救信號\N{\rENG}and see if I could signal for help.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:46.11,1:31:48.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,就從這邊走  你可以過來幫我...\N{\rENG}It's through here. Come and help.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:48.31,1:31:51.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,停下  不能去樓頂\N{\rENG}Hold it. Forget the roof.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.18,1:31:55.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,我說了  不能去樓頂  到處都是他們的人\N{\rENG}I said forget the roof. They got people all over it.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:56.42,1:31:58.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,你要是想活命  就和我在一起\N{\rENG}You wanna stay alive, you stay with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.72,1:32:03.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們現在只知道\N{\rENG}The best we can figure it,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:03.86,1:32:07.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,也許在第30層有大約\N{\rENG}we've got maybe 30 or 35 hostages up there,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:07.43,1:32:09.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,30到35名人質\N{\rENG}probably on the 30th floor,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:09.43,1:32:13.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,和大概七八個匪徒\N{\rENG}and maybe seven or eight terrorists up there.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:13.13,1:32:15.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,聽起來好像是A-7狀況\N{\rENG}Sounds like an A-7 scenario.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.40,1:32:17.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝  從現在開始由我們接管\N{\rENG}Thank you. We'll handle it from here.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:17.90,1:32:20.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,需要用你的人時  我會通知你的\N{\rENG}When we commandeer your men, we'll try and let you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:20.84,1:32:22.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,你是不是忘了點什麼?\N{\rENG}Aren't you forgetting something?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.88,1:32:23.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,什麼?\N{\rENG}Such as?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:23.94,1:32:25.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,約翰·麥克萊恩呢?\N{\rENG}What about John McClane?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.68,1:32:28.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,有他  才有我們剛才那些資料\N{\rENG}He's the reason we have any information.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:28.92,1:32:32.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,有他  你們要對付的只剩七個  而不是十二個匪徒\N{\rENG}He's also the reason you're facing seven terrorists, not twelve.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:32.62,1:32:34.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,他在裡面?他是誰?\N{\rENG}He's inside? Who is he?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.05,1:32:37.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,他也許是個員警  我們正在核實\N{\rENG}He might be a cop. We're checking on that.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:38.06,1:32:40.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,-是你的人?  -不  絕對不是\N{\rENG}- One of yours? - No, no way.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:46.27,1:32:47.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,你抽煙嗎?\N{\rENG}You smoke?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.67,1:32:50.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,對\N{\rENG}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:54.91,1:32:56.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝\N{\rENG}Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:59.98,1:33:02.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,你不是中富公司的\N{\rENG}You don't work for Nakatomi.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.15,1:33:10.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,你也不是恐怖分子\N{\rENG}And if you're not one of them...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:12.13,1:33:14.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是紐約員警\N{\rENG}I'm a cop from New York.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:15.46,1:33:17.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,紐約?\N{\rENG}New York?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.13,1:33:18.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,對\N{\rENG}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:19.13,1:33:21.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,陰差陽錯來參加這個晚會\N{\rENG}Got invited to the Christmas party by mistake.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:22.07,1:33:23.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒想到\N{\rENG}Who knew?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:31.95,1:33:35.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,總比光著屁股被抓到好\N{\rENG}Better than being caught with your pants down, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:43.32,1:33:44.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,我叫約翰·麥克萊恩\N{\rENG}I'm John McClane.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:46.13,1:33:47.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,你是...\N{\rENG}You're?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:49.00,1:33:50.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,克雷\N{\rENG}Clay.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:52.60,1:33:53.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,比爾·克雷\N{\rENG}Bill Clay.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:00.11,1:34:02.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,知道怎麼用手槍嗎  比爾?\N{\rENG}Know how to use a handgun, Bill?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:03.58,1:34:05.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,我曾在野戰營過了一星期\N{\rENG}I spent a weekend at a combat ranch.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:05.65,1:34:07.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,你知道那種  發射紅色顏料球的槍嗎?\N{\rENG}That game with the guns that shoot red paint.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:08.01,1:34:10.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,也許對你來說有點傻\N{\rENG}Probably seems kind of stupid to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:11.65,1:34:12.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,不\N{\rENG}Nope.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.99,1:34:17.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,要動真格的了  比爾\N{\rENG}Time for the real thing, Bill.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:26.37,1:34:28.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,扣下扳機就對了\N{\rENG}All you gotta do is pull the trigger.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:29.34,1:34:29.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,走吧\N{\rENG}Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:49.36,1:34:53.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,把槍放下  把雷管還給我\N{\rENG}Put down the gun and give me my detonators.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:58.06,1:34:59.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,看看是誰\N{\rENG}Well, well, well...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:01.43,1:35:02.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,漢斯\N{\rENG}Hans.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:03.50,1:35:06.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,把槍放下  馬上\N{\rENG}Put it down now.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.64,1:35:13.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,裝出那種口音的確不簡單\N{\rENG}That's pretty tricky with that accent.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:13.25,1:35:16.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,你應該上電視表演\N{\rENG}You oughta be on fucking TV with that accent.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:18.72,1:35:22.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,你要這些雷管想幹什麼?\N{\rENG}But what do you want with the detonators?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:22.46,1:35:25.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,我已經用光了所有炸藥\N{\rENG}I already used all the explosives.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:27.46,1:35:28.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,是嗎?\N{\rENG}Or did I?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:30.26,1:35:31.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,我只數到三\N{\rENG}I'm going to count to three.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:31.93,1:35:34.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,對了  就像對高木那樣?\N{\rENG}Yeah. Like you did with Takagi?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.10,1:35:39.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒有子彈\N{\rENG}No bullets.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:39.51,1:35:42.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,你以為我很蠢嗎  漢斯?\N{\rENG}What do you think... I'm fuckin' stupid, Hans?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:42.68,1:35:43.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,你說呢?\N{\rENG}You were saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:48.71,1:36:50.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,打碎玻璃\N{\rENG}Shoot the glass!
Dialogue: 0,1:37:23.98,1:37:25.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,王八蛋!\N{\rENG}Jesus Christ!
Dialogue: 0,1:37:54.74,1:37:57.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,笑吧  卡爾  我們又開張了\N{\rENG}Smile, Karl. We're back in business.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:00.38,1:38:03.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,是外交的最後手段\N{\rENG}is the last resort of diplomacy,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:03.45,1:38:06.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們或許可以這麼說\N{\rENG}then couldn't we just as well say
Dialogue: 0,1:38:06.59,1:38:09.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,恐怖主義也有同樣的效果\N{\rENG}that terrorism has an equal claim on being that, too?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:10.19,1:38:12.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,告訴我你找到什麼了?\N{\rENG}Tell me you got something.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:12.43,1:38:16.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,只有麥克萊恩的名字  警徽號  任職記錄  基本資料\N{\rENG}McClane's name, badge number, employment record, vital statistics,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:16.46,1:38:18.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,和他家人的地址\N{\rENG}and his family's home address
Dialogue: 0,1:38:19.03,1:38:20.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,就在洛杉磯這裡\N{\rENG}right here in LA.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:28.67,1:38:29.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,去工作\N{\rENG}Go to work.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:30.04,1:38:31.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,明白\N{\rENG}Got it.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:43.99,1:38:47.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,天哪  那個人好像真的很生氣\N{\rENG}God, that man looks really pissed.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:49.60,1:38:51.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,他還活著\N{\rENG}He's still alive.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:51.93,1:38:52.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,什麼?\N{\rENG}What?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:53.30,1:38:57.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,只有約翰才能把人逼成那樣\N{\rENG}Only John can drive somebody that crazy.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:14.12,1:39:18.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,漢斯  快帶你的奇跡來  我們剛打開第六道\N{\rENG}Hans, heat up that miracle because we just broke through on number six...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:18.52,1:39:21.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,電磁密封突然就啟動了\N{\rENG}and the electromagnetic came down like an anvil.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:21.29,1:39:26.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,很好  先看看窗外的朋友  在幹什麼  我馬上就到\N{\rENG}Have a look at what our friends outside are doing and I'll be right up.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:29.07,1:39:30.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,嘿  約翰\N{\rENG}Hey, John.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:30.30,1:39:32.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,約翰·麥克萊恩  你還在嗎?\N{\rENG}John McClane, you still with us?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:32.84,1:39:33.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,在\N{\rENG}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:34.74,1:39:38.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,不過要是讓我選  我寧願到費城去\N{\rENG}But all things being equal, I'd rather be in Philadelphia.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:39.14,1:39:41.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,又幹掉兩個壞蛋\N{\rENG}Chalk up two more bad guys.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.65,1:39:44.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,很高興聽到這消息\N{\rENG}The boys down here will be glad to hear that.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:45.28,1:39:47.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,知道嗎  我們都在你身上下了注\N{\rENG}We got a pool going on you.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:47.25,1:39:49.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,我現在的賠率是多少?\N{\rENG}What kind of odds am I getting?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:49.19,1:39:50.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,你最好別知道\N{\rENG}You don't want to know.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:50.95,1:39:52.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,幫我下20塊\N{\rENG}Put me down for 20.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:52.49,1:39:53.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,我賠得起\N{\rENG}I'm good for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:57.56,1:40:00.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,鮑爾  你是平足嗎?\N{\rENG}Hey, pal, you got flat feet?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:02.73,1:40:04.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,你這是什麼意思  夥計?\N{\rENG}What the hell you talking about, man?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:05.00,1:40:07.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,你為什麼不幹巡警了?\N{\rENG}Something had to get you off the street.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:07.54,1:40:08.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,這有什麼?\N{\rENG}What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:08.81,1:40:12.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,你認為在辦公桌後面  整理檔就不是員警了嗎?\N{\rENG}You don't think a desk job is a noble effort for a cop?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:13.98,1:40:15.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,不\N{\rENG}No.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:18.72,1:40:20.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,我出過一次意外\N{\rENG}I had an accident.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:20.82,1:40:23.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,像你那樣開車肯定得出事\N{\rENG}The way you drive, I can see why.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:23.19,1:40:23.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,是什麼事故?\N{\rENG}What'd you do?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:24.02,1:40:26.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,開車軋了隊長的腳嗎?\N{\rENG}Run over your captain's foot with the car?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:30.49,1:40:31.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,我殺了一個孩子\N{\rENG}I shot a kid.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:33.30,1:40:35.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,他當時只有13歲\N{\rENG}He was 13 years old.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:36.37,1:40:40.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,天很黑  我看不清楚  他拿著逼真的玩具槍\N{\rENG}Oh, it was dark. I couldn't see him. He had a ray gun, looked real enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:43.71,1:40:47.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,員警學校  把你從菜鳥教成老手\N{\rENG}When you're a rookie, they teach you everything about being a cop
Dialogue: 0,1:40:47.11,1:40:49.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,卻沒教你怎麼背下責任\N{\rENG}except how to live with a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:53.38,1:40:58.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,總之  我再也無法  用槍指著任何人了\N{\rENG}Anyway, I just couldn't bring myself to draw my gun on anybody again.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:01.22,1:41:02.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,抱歉  夥計\N{\rENG}Sorry, man.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:04.06,1:41:06.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,嘿  夥計  你能體會嗎?\N{\rENG}Hey, man, how could you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:09.13,1:41:10.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,我現在感覺很糟\N{\rENG}I feel like shit anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:13.97,1:41:15.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,那我還是告訴你吧\N{\rENG}Well, this won't matter.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:15.64,1:41:20.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在不是洛杉磯員警掌舵了\N{\rENG}DoThe LAPD is not calling the shots down here anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:22.85,1:41:24.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,調查局?\N{\rENG}The Feds?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:24.55,1:41:25.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,你說對了\N{\rENG}You got it.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:28.29,1:41:30.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,你看  這些是市政工程師\N{\rENG}Those are the city engineers.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:30.75,1:41:31.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,等等\N{\rENG}Wait.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:32.29,1:41:35.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們在查看街道電路\N{\rENG}They're going into the street circuits.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:35.09,1:41:37.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,看那些穿西裝的傢伙  不知是幹什麼的\N{\rENG}The guys in suits, I don't know who they are.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:37.39,1:41:38.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,那就是調查局的\N{\rENG}That's the FBI.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:39.23,1:41:42.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們依照程式  下令切斷大廈的電源\N{\rENG}They're ordering the others to cut the building's power.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:42.90,1:41:44.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,象發條一樣規律\N{\rENG}Regular as clockwork.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:46.77,1:41:48.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,就象一把鑰匙\N{\rENG}Or a time lock.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:48.84,1:41:50.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,正確\N{\rENG}Precisely.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:50.67,1:41:54.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,為了對抗一起恐怖活動...\N{\rENG}The circuits that cannot be cut are cut automatically...
Dialogue: 0,1:41:54.58,1:41:57.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,無法切斷的電路  於是被迫切斷了\N{\rENG}in response to a terrorist incident.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:57.41,1:41:58.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,想要奇跡  西奧  就去找...\N{\rENG}You asked for miracles, Theo.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:59.62,1:42:02.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,聯邦調查局\N{\rENG}I give you the F-B-I.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:03.95,1:42:05.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,我要你切斷這座大廈的電源!\N{\rENG}I want the building shut down.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:05.31,1:42:07.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,-我這兒有點問題  -我不管你有什麼問題!\N{\rENG}- I got a problem. - I don't care about your problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:07.22,1:42:09.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,-這個開關  -我不管你什麼爛開關\N{\rENG}- I got a switch... - I don't care about your switch.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:09.67,1:42:12.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,我要這座大樓斷電  達克\N{\rENG}I want the building out. Dark!
Dialogue: 0,1:42:12.80,1:42:14.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,你不明白  不能從這兒切斷\N{\rENG}You don't understand. You can't do it from here.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:14.73,1:42:17.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,-我們可以  -不能在這兒切斷\N{\rENG}- Yeah, you could. - It can't be done from here.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:17.23,1:42:18.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,我可以  我有對講機\N{\rENG}I could... I got the radio...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:18.34,1:42:22.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,只能從市中心切斷\N{\rENG}It's got to be done from downtown.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:22.54,1:42:26.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,整個電網都會斷電  這關係到十個街區\N{\rENG}They've gotta take out a whole city grid. We're talking 10 square blocks.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:26.41,1:42:28.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,十個街區?  天哪  強森  你瘋了嗎?\N{\rENG}Ten blocks? Johnson, that's crazy.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:28.12,1:42:30.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,今天是聖誕夜  成千上萬的人\N{\rENG}It's Christmas Eve. There's thousands of people.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:30.61,1:42:31.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們必須這樣做!\N{\rENG}You have to go wider.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:32.85,1:42:36.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,-我需要授權!  -美國政府授權還不夠嗎?\N{\rENG}- I need authorization. - How about the United States government?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:37.18,1:42:39.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,切斷電網  要麼丟掉飯碗\N{\rENG}Lose the grid, or you lose yourjob.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:45.89,1:42:47.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,中心嗎?\N{\rENG}Yeah, Central?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:47.76,1:42:50.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是沃爾特  在中富大廈\N{\rENG}This is Walt, down at Nakatomi.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:50.16,1:42:55.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,聽著  你幫我切斷212電網好嗎?\N{\rENG}Would it be possible for you to turn off grid 212?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:55.17,1:42:56.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,你瘋了嗎?\N{\rENG}Are you crazy?!
Dialogue: 0,1:42:56.40,1:42:59.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,也許我該給市長打個電話\N{\rENG}Maybe I should call the mayor.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:59.14,1:43:02.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,倒楣的是我  我這兒麻煩大了  快關掉\N{\rENG}No shit it's my ass. I got a big problem here. Shut it down.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:02.31,1:43:04.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,切斷電源  馬上!\N{\rENG}Shut it down now.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:07.98,1:43:10.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,啟動緊急電源\N{\rENG}Emergency lighting activated.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:10.82,1:43:13.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,鮑爾!  回答我  這是怎麼回事?\N{\rENG}Al, talk to me. What's going on here?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:13.75,1:43:15.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,去問調查局吧\N{\rENG}Ask the FBI.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:15.35,1:43:18.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們正拿著反恐怖指南\N{\rENG}They got the universal terrorist playbook
Dialogue: 0,1:43:18.19,1:43:20.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,按部就班地照辦\N{\rENG}and they're running it step by step.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:22.76,1:43:24.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,要打開了  要開了!\N{\rENG}It's gonna go. It's gonna go!
Dialogue: 0,1:43:26.50,1:43:27.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,好的!\N{\rENG}Yes!
Dialogue: 0,1:43:50.76,1:43:52.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,聖誕快樂!\N{\rENG}Merry Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:53.76,1:43:56.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,那幫雜種可能已經尿了褲子了\N{\rENG}They must be pissing in their pants.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:57.00,1:43:58.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,市長會殺了我\N{\rENG}The mayor is gonna have my ass.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:21.54,1:44:23.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在我們該怎麼辦?\N{\rENG}What are we gonna do now?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:23.33,1:44:25.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,因為拒付電費逮捕他們嗎?\N{\rENG}Arrest them for not paying their electric bill?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:26.01,1:44:27.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,把他們關在裡面\N{\rENG}We've shut them down.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:27.85,1:44:31.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,讓他們流點冷汗  然後給他們直升機\N{\rENG}We let them sweat for a while, then we give them helicopters.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:31.38,1:44:33.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,一個不留\N{\rENG}Right up the ass.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:36.19,1:44:37.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是強森探員\N{\rENG}This is Agent Johnson.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:37.79,1:44:39.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,不  是另一個\N{\rENG}No, the other one.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:39.26,1:44:42.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,我需要空中支援在五分鐘內出發\N{\rENG}I want that air support ready to lift off in five minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:42.63,1:44:46.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒錯  全副武裝  我們馬上就到\N{\rENG}Damn right. Fully armed. We're on the way.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:52.04,1:44:53.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,耶!\N{\rENG}Oh, yes!
Dialogue: 0,1:44:55.64,1:44:58.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,我要和聯邦調查局的人談\N{\rENG}I wish to talk to the FBI.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:00.65,1:45:02.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是特別探員強森\N{\rENG}This is Special Agent Johnson.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:02.85,1:45:07.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,州政府已經安排你的同志們回家了\N{\rENG}The State Department has arranged for the return of your comrades.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:07.42,1:45:10.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,直升機馬上就到  按照你的要求\N{\rENG}Helicopters are en route as you requested.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:10.12,1:45:11.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,我知道了  我們正在準備\N{\rENG}I hear you. We'll be ready.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:12.46,1:45:14.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,等他知道上當的時候  已經在屍袋裡了\N{\rENG}When he figures out what hit him, he'll be in a body bag.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:15.69,1:45:18.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們一著陸  我們就炸了樓頂\N{\rENG}When they touch down, we'll blow the roof.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:18.66,1:45:23.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,等他們查出原因  我們已經在海灘上吃紅利了\N{\rENG}By the time they figure it all out, we'll be sitting on a beach earning 20%.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:29.89,1:45:31.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,媽的!\N{\rENG}Ah! Jeez!
Dialogue: 0,1:45:31.49,1:45:32.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,鮑爾?\N{\rENG}Powell?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:33.36,1:45:34.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,嘿  鮑爾  你有空嗎?\N{\rENG}Yo, Powell, you got a minute?
