Dialogue: 0,2:00:41.45,2:00:43.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,為什麼要炸掉整座大樓  漢斯?\N{\rENG}Why'd you have to nuke the whole building?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:43.86,2:00:46.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果你偷了六百塊  你可以馬上消失\N{\rENG}Well, when you steal $600, you can just disappear.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:46.96,2:00:49.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果你偷的是六億  他們肯定能找到你\N{\rENG}When you steal 600 million, they will find you...
Dialogue: 0,2:00:50.06,2:00:52.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,除非他們認為你已經死了\N{\rENG}unless they think you're already dead.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:52.40,2:00:54.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,把槍放下\N{\rENG}Put down the gun.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:05.01,2:01:06.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,不  他是我的\N{\rENG}This is mine.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:09.95,2:01:11.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,你贏了\N{\rENG}You got me.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:11.88,2:01:14.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,還是牛仔作風  麥克萊恩先生\N{\rENG}Still the cowboy, Mr McClane.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:14.75,2:01:16.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,美國人都一樣\N{\rENG}Americans... all alike.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:16.49,2:01:20.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,不過這次約翰·韋恩別想和格雷斯·凱麗一起出去看落日了\N{\rENG}This time, John Wayne does not walk off into the sunset with Grace Kelly.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:20.53,2:01:22.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,應該是加里·庫珀  笨蛋\N{\rENG}That was Gary Cooper, asshole.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:22.43,2:01:24.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,玩笑開夠了\N{\rENG}Enough jokes.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:24.33,2:01:27.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,你自己也能成為好牛仔  漢斯\N{\rENG}You'd have made a pretty good cowboy yourself, Hans.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:27.30,2:01:31.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的  你以前對我是怎麼說的\N{\rENG}Oh, yes. What was it you said to me before?
Dialogue: 0,2:01:32.04,2:01:35.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,去你媽的  王八蛋\N{\rENG}Yippee-ki-yay, motherfucker.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:56.96,2:01:57.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,荷莉\N{\rENG}Holly!
Dialogue: 0,2:02:03.54,2:02:04.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,旅途愉快  漢斯\N{\rENG}Happy trails, Hans.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:49.72,2:02:51.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,希望那不是一名人質\N{\rENG}I hope that's not a hostage.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:27.65,2:03:29.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,那邊的角度更好\N{\rENG}Over here. It's a better angle.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:30.29,2:03:31.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,過去幫他們一把\N{\rENG}Let's give them a hand.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:33.96,2:03:37.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,繼續  現在繼續\N{\rENG}Keep it going, now. Keep it going.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:42.07,2:03:45.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,-快點  要錯過了  -把手稿遞給我\N{\rENG}- Come on. We're going to miss it! - OK. Hand me my notes!
Dialogue: 0,2:04:08.69,2:04:12.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,當時裡面什麼狀況  他們如何對待你們的?\N{\rENG}What was it like in there? How did they treat you?
Dialogue: 0,2:04:59.01,2:05:00.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是我太太  荷莉\N{\rENG}Al, this is my wife Holly.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:00.81,2:05:02.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,荷莉·吉奈蘿\N{\rENG}Holly Gennero.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:03.52,2:05:04.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,荷莉·麥克萊恩\N{\rENG}Holly McClane.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:05.10,2:05:06.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,你好  荷莉\N{\rENG}Hello, Holly.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:06.80,2:05:08.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,你選了一個好丈夫\N{\rENG}You got yourself a good man.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:08.90,2:05:10.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,你要好好照顧他\N{\rENG}You take good care of him.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:11.79,2:05:12.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,麥克萊恩\N{\rENG}McClane!
Dialogue: 0,2:05:13.56,2:05:16.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,麥克萊恩  我要聽你的簡報\N{\rENG}McClane, I want a debriefing!
Dialogue: 0,2:05:16.20,2:05:18.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,你必須回答一些問題  先生\N{\rENG}You got some things to answer for, mister.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:18.96,2:05:20.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,殺死艾利斯是一件\N{\rENG}Ellis' murder, for one thing.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:20.77,2:05:24.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,財產損失  妨礙警方公務\N{\rENG}Property damage, interfering with police business.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:04.88,2:06:07.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,你們兩個進去看看  還有沒有別的人\N{\rENG}Two of you go inside and see if there's anybody else!
Dialogue: 0,2:06:18.72,2:06:21.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是自己人!\N{\rENG}No. This one's with me.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:31.27,2:06:32.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,麥克萊恩先生  麥克萊恩先生!\N{\rENG}Mr McClane, Mr McClane!
Dialogue: 0,2:06:32.94,2:06:36.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,一切都結束了  經過這些折磨  你有什麼感想?\N{\rENG}Now that it's all over, after this incredible ordeal, what are your feelings?
Dialogue: 0,2:06:42.81,2:06:44.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,看誰來了\N{\rENG}Well, well, well.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:45.32,2:06:47.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,-聖誕快樂  阿蓋  -聖誕快樂\N{\rENG}- Merry Christmas, Argyle. - Merry Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:52.12,2:06:53.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,你拍下來了?\N{\rENG}Did you get that?
Dialogue: 0,2:06:55.73,2:06:59.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果這就是他們的耶誕節  我明年一定還來\N{\rENG}If this is their idea of Christmas, I gotta be here for New Year's.

